dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.transportprotocols

Interface IJ1939TpConnection

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, ITpConnection

    public interface IJ1939TpConnection
extends IEntity, ITpConnection
    IJ1939TpConnection: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    A J1939TpConnection represents an internal path for the transmission or reception of a Pdu via J1939Tp and describes the sender and the receiver of this particular communication. The J1939Tp module routes a Pdu (J1939 PGN) through the connection.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getFlowControlPdus

        java.util.Set<? extends INPdu> getFlowControlPdus()
        Query the undirectional to-many association FlowControlPdu.

        Reference to the Command NPdus (TP.CM) that are used in the CMDT (Connection Mode Data Transfer) in both directions. BAM uses one TP.CM (Transport Protocol Command). The flowControlNPdu has a fixed length of 8 bytes. Please note that the role name "flowControlIPdu" is misleading and is kept for backward compatibilty reasons.

        Returns:
        the referenced entities
        Throws:
        TresosDBException - in case of an error

        java.util.Set<? extends IIPdu> getTpSdus()
        Query the undirectional to-many association TpSdu.

        Please note that this reference is deprecated and will be removed in the future. This reference is replaced by the J1939TpPg.tpSdu reference. Old description: Reference to IPdus that are segmented by the Transport Protocol. To support the low-level routing of NPdu's the NPdu is a specialization of an IPdu. More details can be found in the NPdu class description. Nevertheless the J1939TpConnection must not reference a NPdu with this tpSdu reference.
